'''Holy Rus''' ({{lang-ru|–°–≤—è—Ç–∞ÃÅ—è –†—É—Å—å}}, ''[[:wikt:—Å–≤—è—Ç–æ–π#Russian|Svyataya]] [[Rus (name)|Rus]]'') is a [[Russian Orthodox Church|Russian Orthodox Christian]] organisation in [[Russia]], headed by Ivan Otrakovsky.<ref name=MoscowNews>{{cite web|last=Lobzina |first=Alina |title=Orthodox activists create Moscow patrol squads |url=http://themoscownews.com/local/20120822/190122832.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120920023225/http://themoscownews.com/local/20120822/190122832.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2012-09-20 |publisher=The Moscow News |date=2012-08-22 |accessdate=2012-08-23 }}</ref> The organisation established an Orthodox Christian patrol squad in August 2012 in order to protect Christian churches from [[desecration]] by [[Vandalism|vandal]]s, informing the police or stopping the criminal if necessary.<ref name=BBC>{{cite web|title=Orthodox activists create Moscow patrol squads|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/russian/society/2012/08/120821_church_activist_squads.shtml|publisher=BBC|date=2012-08-21|accessdate=2012-08-23}}</ref><ref name=RT>{{cite web|title=‚ÄòJail for sacrilege‚Äô: Vandalism by Pussy Riot supporters angers MPs|url=http://rt.com/politics/sacrilege-law-church-punishment-272/|publisher=Russia Today|date=2012-08-22|accessdate=2012-08-23}}</ref> In addition, the squads also deal with individuals who [[sneer]] at [[Minister (Christianity)|priests]].<ref name="BBC"/><ref name="RT"/> The leader of the group, Ivan Otrakovsky, stated that: {{blockquote|The time has come to remind all [[Apostasy in Christianity|apostate]]s and [[theomachist]]s that it is our land and we forbid [[blasphemy|blasphemous]], offensive actions and statements against the Orthodox religion and our people. An Orthodox believer in God is very calm and moderate. We don‚Äôt have any personal enemies, just the enemies of faith.<ref name="MoscowNews"/><ref name="BBC"/>}} Holy Rus stated that its patrol squads will also target individuals insulting God or displaying [[sacrilegious]] symbols, such as an [[inverted cross]].<ref name="Le Courrier de Russie">{{cite web|title=Les miliciens orthodoxes d√©clarent ouverte la chasse aux h√©r√©tiques|url=http://www.lecourrierderussie.com/2012/08/22/les-miliciens-orthodoxes-declarent-ouverte-la-chasse-aux-heretiques/|publisher=Le Courrier de Russie|date=2012-08-22|accessdate=2012-08-22}}</ref> There are currently seven volunteer squads operating in Russia and the number is expected to grow.<ref name="BBC"/> "Blasphemy, heresy, defilement and lechery" are offences that Holy Rus will aim to curb.<ref name="Le Courrier de Russie"/> Holy Rus is supported by the majority of the clergy, [[Forbes]] reported.<ref>{{cite web|title="Orthodox Activists" Are Going To Patrol Moscow: What Could Possibly Go Wrong?|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/markadomanis/2012/08/22/orthodox-activists-are-going-to-patrol-moscow-what-could-possibly-go-wrong/|publisher=Forbes|date=2012-08-22|accessdate=2012-08-22}}</ref>
